column5: Ive got to do a bit of writing on the opportunities on Lake Nosbonsing for the various species:  Any on here that has fished the lake enough to help with some answers??
TJ - Pm FishnSled, he's been fishing it a bit lately. HH
It's been a few years now but I fished it regularly each summer.

Nothing in many years. My former Father in Law had a Walleye honey hole there he had been going to since he was a kid. We would go from Nip to there for at least 1 day during the summer. Same exact presentations as Calendar Bay, troll worm harnesses and white or yellow stand up jig with worms and trailer hooks, pretty simple.

These are the questions I am doing a survey on.  I have to do some serious descriptions I have to write up for a client.  Can you answer these questions to the best of your ability??  Im getting input from a bunch of people and will average it out lol...  thanks again!!
I have an internet buddy who lives on Nosbonsing, and doesn't fish! Builds model aircraft instead. One of these days I'll convince him that it's possible to do both.
